RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 73. Allowance Purse 36000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR TWO YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since October 9 Allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIDGET chased the pace from the two path into the backstretch, moved to vie for the lead with pacesetter nearing the half-mile pole, inched past the dueler into mid-turn and was joined by another, dueled with that one through the lane while drifting to the rail and inched clear late. CHISPARRAJOS chased the pace from the three path down the backstretch, bid with the winner in mid-turn while three wide, dueled with that one until late then could not keep up while well clear for the place spot. TAKEITANDRUN was five wide through the first turn, continued well off the inside into the far turn, bid with the runner-up while in the four or five path through the turn then could not keep up with the top two. ASTRONOMICO set the pace down the backstretch, was joined by the winner late on backstretch, dueled to mid-turn then gave way. CROWNED JEWEL was in the two path through the turns and lacked a response. COWBOY CHURCH chased the pace from along the inside and was done on the turn. NATIONS DREAM raced four wide into the first turn, continued in the three path through the far turn and was never in it. INNOCENT MAN stumbled badly at the start, dropped back to trail and never responded.

ENTRY.NAME: Fidget
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 2path, vied 1/2-3/8, dueled to late, cleared

ENTRY.NAME: Chisparrajos
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased 3path, bid 3wd turn, dueled, yielded late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUIMICHIS set the pace while under pressure from both sides and in the two path, cleared in late turn and into the lane while in the four path, slowly drifted in to the two path near the eighth pole and was kept to the task while under a hand ride late. QUALIFICATA was close up early while near the inside, came off the inside into the lane, guided to the three path near the eighth pole and was slowly gaining to the end. MUSICAL DIVA pressed the winner from the three path through mid-turn, came into the lane from the four path and lacked a closing response. CHIP SHORTAGE leaned in at the start, settled to the back and trailed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 4 5F Turf CR: 80. Allowance Purse 36000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $10,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, STATE BRED OR INDIANA BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 5 furlongs on the main track. (Rail at 36 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RILEYS REDEMPTION pressed the pace outside of the leader, bid at the eighth pole and drew off under steady urging. KENDAL GRACE was off awkwardly, raced in the two path, bid at the eighth pole but was no threat. MAGIC BEAUTY led inside before giving way at the eighth pole. SECRET OPERATION had a mild late bid outside. MORE THAN A DIVA saved ground before fading in the stretch. POND WALKER (GB) raced inside and had no late bid. STRAWBERRYLEMONADE stalked the pace in the three path before fading. DEEP DISH was bumped at the start, stalked the early pace between foes, then faded. GOGO GEISHA was not a factor. ROYAL DIAMOND was bumped at the start.

ENTRY.OWNER: Nicks William and Klopp Randy L

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 71. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track. (Rail at 36 fe et).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SARGENT HULKA chased the early pace into the backstretch, moved to vie for the lead into the turn, was joined by the runner-up in mid-turn, dueled with that one into the lane, lost the lead near the eighth pole then battled back to inch up late. NINE POINTER settled off the early pace while off the inside, bid from the three path approaching mid-turn, dueled with the top one from there to deep stretch, could not stay late and settled for second best. BIGLEY HUGE chased the pace from the three or four path through the turn, lost touch with the top two into the lane then won the duel for the show spot. YOSHIDA'S IMPACT raced in the two path through the turn and into the lane, dueled with the show rival through the lane and could not prevail. STAR REVIEW raced in mid-pack into the turn while off the rail, was three wide and between rivals in late turn, came into the lane from the four or five path and never was a threat. CHARMING VICTORY never a factor while racing in the four to five path through the turns. THREE TWO RUN raced in the three or four path through the turn when near the back, came into the lane from the six path and never menaced. CROSSROADSCORREDOR vied for the lead along the inside into the far turn and was suddenly done. HAYWES chased the pace from the three path into the turn and was empty in late turn. DE LA VICTORY raced along the inside throughout and steadily lost ground. ADAMANTLY CROSS rushed out of the gate down the front stretch, continued a straight route to the outside rail into the turn and was pulled up entering the backstretch and walked off.

ENTRY.COMMENT: bolted 1st turn, pulled up, walked off

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, bid 3path turn, dueled, yielded late, 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR THREE YEAR OLDS. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 9 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIERCE JUSTICE pressed the pace two wide into the turn, was between rivals through late turn and into the lane, was in a bit tight straightening in the lane, continued between rivals through the final eighth and inched up in a game effort. CONQUERED vied three wide through the far turn, came into the lane still three wide, gained the lead outside the eighth pole then could not hold the winner safe while saving the place spot. KINGOFTHERAINBOW vied for the lead along the inside of two others through the turn and into the lane, was still a serious threat with a furlong to run and could not keep up late. BOLD BIZNESS saved ground through the turn, came into the lane from the two path, shifted into the four path inside the eighth pole and was gaining. UNBRIDLED VICTOR was in the three path through the turn and into the lane and offered belated energy to be gaining too late. MACHO ALEGRE raced in the two path through the turn when never far back, came into the lane from the five path and weakened in the drive. WISHY WASHY never a factor while along the inside through the turn. OVERTHETOPJUSTICE raced in the three or four path through the turn, came into the lane from the six path and never was a menace. ROYAL ICING was close up early, continued in the four path through the turn and faded through the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOSPEL MUSIC set the pace under pressure into the turn, cleared in mid-turn, came into the lane from the three path, was engaged outside the furlong pole then repelled the runner-up and widened late. PEWTER'S PROMISE bid three wide through the turn, came into the lane from the four path, moved to loom a serious threat with a furlong to go then could not keep up late while finishing clear for the place spot. FLAT OUT DIAMONDS was angled to the rail soon after the start, hustled up to contend through the turn and into the lane then lacked the needed response through the final eighth. CHANNAH DEL MAR raced in the two path through the turn when in mid-pack, came into the lane from the four path and never was a serious threat. OUTLAW WOMAN was bothered at the start and settled in the rear, raced well back into the turn while in the three or four path, came into the lane from the six path and showed interest while moving up. WHO NOT WHAT never a factor while along the inside. KAM'S ROCKIN GOLD pressed the winner two wide into the turn, continued a threat into late turn then was done entering the lane. MORNING REFLECTION raced in the three or four path through the turn when never far back then was empty into the lane. BANDIT QUEEN raced in the four path throughout and was done entering the turn.
